    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-lee-pce-pcep-ls-optical-11.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-lee-pce-pcep-ls-optical-11.txt</link>
        <title>"PCEP Extension for Distribution of Link-State and TE Information for Optical Networks", Young Lee, Haomian Zheng, Daniele Ceccarelli, Wei Wang, Peter Park, Bin-Yeong Yoon</title>
        <dc:date>2022-03-07T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>In order to compute and provide optimal paths, Path Computation Elements (PCEs) require an accurate and timely Traffic Engineering Database (TED). Traditionally this Link State and TE information has been obtained from a link state routing protocol (supporting traffic engineering extensions).  An existing experimental document extends the Path Computation Element Communication Protocol (PCEP) with Link-State and Traffic Engineering (TE) Information.  This document provides further experimental extensions to collect Link-State and TE information for optical networks.</description>
    </item>
